    "Review findingsIn this section we aimed to present a nuanced understanding of the current landscape of AI-driven cyberattacks, including the motivations behind such attacks, the mitigation strategies available, and the broader societal implications.",
    "Through an in-depth analysis of 18 rigorously selected papers, we answered the five research questions of the paper.",
    "Types of AI-driven cyberattacksThe paper's first research objective was to identify the different ways in which AI can be used to launch cyberattacks.",
    "The offensive AI (deploys AI techniques to attack computer systems and networks) and adversarial AI (maliciously exploits and/or attacks AI/ML systems and data) findings are presented in Table 5 and 6, respectively.Having outlined the landscape of both offensive AI and its specialised subset, adversarial AI, we now discuss the countermeasures and mitigation strategies that can be deployed to defend against these advanced threats.",
